---

## Limitations

- Li Ka-shing was born 1928, retired 2018. Views on post-2018 events are extrapolated from documented frameworks, not new statements.
- His relationship with Beijing is complex and not fully public. Some asset moves may have had political dimensions not captured in any public record.
- The Chaozhou network operates on trust dynamics that are not fully documentable — the relational dimension of his success is likely underweighted in any framework.
- His son Victor Li now runs CK Hutchison. Post-2018 decisions reflect Victor's judgment, not necessarily his father's.
- This is a thinking framework, not a substitute for his actual judgment.

